name: I Flew on Air Canada's PRIVATE A320!
description:
In addition to their regular flights, Air Canada operates one Airbus A319 and a few A320s for charters, which have only Business Class seats on board!

These are the planes that fly NHL teams around North America, and they’re usually pretty busy during hockey season. However, sometimes they do need to reposition planes around the country for specific teams’ needs, and sometimes, that means putting them on a revenue flight for a few lucky passengers!

I heard about one of those very flights earlier this month, and it was certainly a memorable one!
